  ('8493c1a3-0fa4-55b7-bd9d-4a6c40b139af', 'TEL-RF-012', 'IND_TLC_D13', 'TEL-ROLE-032', 'Interconnect Operations Specialist operates in NLD/ILD Capacity, Interconnect, and Leased Bandwidth Coordination, focusing on coordinating carrier handoffs, routing readiness, test windows and capacity acceptance across operator boundaries. The role uses capacity inventory, utilization dashboards, interconnect records, carrier partner notes, reservation files and route continuity evidence to confirm facts, coordinate the right owner, document service or deployment impact, and close work only after telecom validation evidence is captured.', 'I', 'E', 'C', 'IEC', 'Interconnect Operations Specialist fits IEC because the role combines investigative action, enterprising diagnosis and conventional evidence control in NLD/ILD Capacity, Interconnect, and Leased Bandwidth Coordination. It requires telecom-specific judgement over coordinating carrier handoffs, routing readiness, test windows and capacity acceptance across operator boundaries, using capacity inventory, utilization dashboards, interconnect records, carrier partner notes, reservation files and route continuity evidence before escalating, restoring, accepting or closing the work.', 'Interconnect Operations Specialist reviews capacity inventory, utilization dashboards, interconnect records, carrier partner notes, reservation files and route continuity evidence; checks whether the current evidence supports coordinating carrier handoffs, routing readiness, test windows and capacity acceptance across operator boundaries; separates confirmed facts from assumptions; records the service, customer, site, capacity, compliance or safety impact; updates the correct ticket, tracker, checklist or handoff note; and closes only after validation proof is attached.', 'Interconnect Operations Specialist works in NLD/ILD Capacity, Interconnect, and Leased Bandwidth Coordination under TEL-RF-012. The day-to-day context includes capacity inventory, utilization dashboards, interconnect records, carrier partner notes, reservation files and route continuity evidence; the role boundary is to validate evidence, coordinate handoffs and support recovery or delivery, not to bypass approved change, regulatory, safety, customer-acceptance or senior engineering authority.', 'Interconnect Operations Specialist: Partner coordination; interconnect status check; test-window tracking; route or capacity handoff; closure confirmation; validates source records; compares expected and actual telecom status; updates the operational system of record; coordinates the field, NOC, vendor, partner, customer or authority owner; prepares exception notes when evidence is incomplete or service risk remains.', 'Interconnect Operations Specialist output evidence includes Carrier handoff log; test result; reservation note; partner closure evidence; a role-specific action note with source record, owner, timestamp, status, blocker and next step; and a closure pack showing before-after status, validation proof and escalation boundary where applicable.', '{"numerical_reasoning": 72.0, "logical_reasoning": 84.0, "verbal_reasoning": 72.0, "spatial_reasoning": 70.0, "data_interpretation": 82.0, "pattern_recognition": 80.0}'::jsonb, '{"openness": 4.0, "extraversion": 3.0, "agreeableness": 4.0, "conscientiousness": 5.0, "emotional_stability": 4.0}'::jsonb, '{"impact": 4.0, "status": 4.0, "autonomy": 4.0, "security": 4.0, "financial": 4.0, "lifestyle": 3.0, "creativity": 4.0, "leadership": 4.0}'::jsonb, '{"areas": ["Logical Reasoning", "Data Interpretation", "Pattern Recognition"], "rationale": "Interconnect Operations Specialist depends most on logical reasoning, data interpretation, pattern recognition because the work involves reading telecom evidence, comparing alarms or test readings, spotting dependency gaps, and deciding whether to dispatch, escalate, validate, recover or hand over the item safely."}'::jsonb, '{"traits": ["Conscientiousness", "Agreeableness", "Emotional Stability"], "rationale": "Interconnect Operations Specialist needs conscientiousness, agreeableness, emotional stability because the role must maintain telecom evidence discipline, remain calm during service-impact pressure, and coordinate reliably with field teams, NOC teams, vendors, customers, carriers or authority stakeholders in NLD/ILD Capacity, Interconnect, and Leased Bandwidth Coordination."}'::jsonb, '{"values": ["Impact", "Leadership", "Financial Growth"], "rationale": "Interconnect Operations Specialist suits learners who value Impact; Leadership; Financial Growth because the role produces visible telecom service impact, stable infrastructure responsibility and measurable recovery, delivery, assurance or stakeholder outcomes. Work values should guide fit and motivation, not replace technical readiness evidence."}'::jsonb, 'Preferred', 'Telecommunications; Electronics and Communication Engineering; Electrical Engineering; Operations; Project Management; Business or Service Delivery', true),
  ('9d1a9e74-899a-5019-92a5-cd6b08bcf748', 'TEL-RF-012', 'IND_TLC_D13', 'TEL-ROLE-033', 'NLD/ILD Operations Engineer operates in NLD/ILD Capacity, Interconnect, and Leased Bandwidth Coordination, focusing on monitoring national or international network paths, partner dependencies and long-distance service continuity evidence. The role uses capacity inventory, utilization dashboards, interconnect records, carrier partner notes, reservation files and route continuity evidence to confirm facts, coordinate the right owner, document service or deployment impact, and close work only after telecom validation evidence is captured.', 'R', 'I', 'C', 'RIC', 'NLD/ILD Operations Engineer fits RIC because the role combines realistic action, investigative diagnosis and conventional evidence control in NLD/ILD Capacity, Interconnect, and Leased Bandwidth Coordination. It requires telecom-specific judgement over monitoring national or international network paths, partner dependencies and long-distance service continuity evidence, using capacity inventory, utilization dashboards, interconnect records, carrier partner notes, reservation files and route continuity evidence before escalating, restoring, accepting or closing the work.', 'NLD/ILD Operations Engineer reviews capacity inventory, utilization dashboards, interconnect records, carrier partner notes, reservation files and route continuity evidence; checks whether the current evidence supports monitoring national or international network paths, partner dependencies and long-distance service continuity evidence; separates confirmed facts from assumptions; records the service, customer, site, capacity, compliance or safety impact; updates the correct ticket, tracker, checklist or handoff note; and closes only after validation proof is attached.', 'NLD/ILD Operations Engineer works in NLD/ILD Capacity, Interconnect, and Leased Bandwidth Coordination under TEL-RF-012. The day-to-day context includes capacity inventory, utilization d