  ('b6b2e3b9-1d54-506c-a5c6-c64ffbb19866', 'TEL-RF-013', 'IND_TLC_D14', 'TEL-ROLE-034', 'Satellite Regulatory Coordinator operates in Satellite Authorization, Frequency Assignment, and VSAT Network Records, focusing on maintaining authorization files, regulatory evidence, frequency records and activation/change compliance exceptions. The role uses authorization trackers, frequency records, technical forms, regulatory references, interference notes and exception routing evidence to confirm facts, coordinate the right owner, document service or deployment impact, and close work only after telecom validation evidence is captured.', 'E', 'C', 'S', 'ECS', 'Satellite Regulatory Coordinator fits ECS because the role combines enterprising action, conventional diagnosis and social evidence control in Satellite Authorization, Frequency Assignment, and VSAT Network Records. It requires telecom-specific judgement over maintaining authorization files, regulatory evidence, frequency records and activation/change compliance exceptions, using authorization trackers, frequency records, technical forms, regulatory references, interference notes and exception routing evidence before escalating, restoring, accepting or closing the work.', 'Satellite Regulatory Coordinator reviews authorization trackers, frequency records, technical forms, regulatory references, interference notes and exception routing evidence; checks whether the current evidence supports maintaining authorization files, regulatory evidence, frequency records and activation/change compliance exceptions; separates confirmed facts from assumptions; records the service, customer, site, capacity, compliance or safety impact; updates the correct ticket, tracker, checklist or handoff note; and closes only after validation proof is attached.', 'Satellite Regulatory Coordinator works in Satellite Authorization, Frequency Assignment, and VSAT Network Records under TEL-RF-013. The day-to-day context includes authorization tracke